laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated, measuring up to 14 mm in diameter with periappendiceal edema and inflammatory change consistent with acute appendicitis. No intra or extrahepatic biliary ductal dilatation. No focal hepatic lesion. No pancreatic ductal dilatation. No splenomegaly. No hydronephrosis. Both ovaries appear unremarkable. No retroperitoneal or mesenteric adenopathy. No suspicious osseous or soft tissue lesion.
